# Eastern region - Clinical Commissioning Groups (CCGs)
Clinical Commissioning Groups (CCGs) are NHS organisations which were set up
to organise the delivery of NHS services in England. Diabetes UK work closely
with these CCGs to ensure the level of healthcare available to people living
with diabetes is of the highest standard and that diabetes is at the top of
the health agenda. There are currently 19 CCGs covering the East of England.
Someone is diagnosed with diabetes every two minutes. Your donation can change
